dcterms:description: The Angle-Delay Channel Power Matrix (ADCPM) is used as a new type of fingerprint for user positioning in massive MIMO-OFDM systems. It captures stable and stationary multipath characteristics, including delay, power, and angle information in both vertical and horizontal directions, which are beneficial for accurate positioning.
dcterms:title: Angle-Delay Channel Power Matrix (ADCPM)

dcterms:creator: X. Wang
L. Gao

dcterms:description: Channel State Information (CSI) is utilized as a fingerprint for indoor localization, capturing rich multipath information that enhances positioning accuracy compared to traditional methods.
dcterms:title: Channel State Information (CSI)

dcterms:description: The QuaDriGa Model is a 3-D multi-cell channel model that incorporates time evolution, enabling virtual field trials for wireless communication systems.
dcterms:title: QuaDriGa Model

dcterms:creator: P. K. et al.
dcterms:description: WINNER II Channel Models provide a comprehensive framework for simulating wireless communication channels, facilitating research and development in mobile communications.
dcterms:title: WINNER II Channel Models

dcterms:description: The 3GPP Urban Macro (UMa) NLOS Scenario is a channel model used for simulating non-line-of-sight conditions in urban environments, aiding in the evaluation of wireless communication systems.
dcterms:title: 3GPP Urban Macro (UMa) NLOS Scenario

dcterms:description: The 3D Channel Model for LTE provides a framework for simulating 3D wireless communication scenarios, enhancing the understanding of channel behavior in LTE networks.
dcterms:title: 3D Channel Model for LTE

dcterms:description: The Channel Model for Frequencies from 0.5 to 100 GHz provides guidelines for simulating wireless channels across a wide frequency range, essential for modern communication systems.
dcterms:title: Channel Model for Frequencies from 0.5 to 100 GHz
